1. Adding Peers

Peers in the local network should be added automaticly using an
UDP broadcast. Many ISP's block UDP broadcasts to the internet, so
there are a few way's to manually add peers.

To add a peer goto the tab 'options'. There you see some options.
If you know the IP address of a peer, just fill it in in the 'Add Peer' box,
and click 'Add'. To add multiple peers at one time, click 'Import Peerlist',
and select an XML peerlist on your local harddrive. 

You can also use 'Download Peerlist' to download and add a peerlist from our
website.

2. Deleting peers

To delete a peer, just go to the 'options' tab, and select the peer you want to
delete in the 'peers' listbox. Then press the 'delete' button.

3. Chatting

All known peers will be added to the chatroom automaticaly. To chat, just enter
your message in the box on the bottom of the 'chat' tab, and press 'send'.

4. Search

To search for files on other peers, just go to the 'search' tab. Here you can 
enter a search string. Click the 'search' button to perform the search. A list
with all the found files will be displayed.

5. Download
To download a file, perform the above operation, and double-click the files you
want to download. You can also select multiple files, by selecting a file and
holding the SHIFT button while you select other files.

6. Play media
To play media, just double-click your finished download. The file will be
automaticaly played by the build in mediaplayer. You can also select 'play file'
from the 'file' menu, and select the file you wish to play. To pause or stop the
the play, right-click the mediaplayer, and select 'pause' or 'stop'.


